gomodel:SYNGO_2533  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: From results section:\nTo identify the potential subcellular site of interaction between 14-3-3 and CaV2.2 channels, we coimmunostained cultured rat hippocampal neurons with either the 14-3-3γ or α1B antibody, together with the synapsin I antibody that specifically labels the presynaptic terminals (Sudhof and Jahn, 1991). Although both 14-3-3γ and α1B subunits distribute broadly in both the somata and neurites, they exhibit extensive costaining with synapsin I in presynaptic terminals (Figure 1B), suggesting that this protein complex may be present in presynaptic terminals and play a role in regulating synaptic transmissions.. Experimental description: From experimental procedures section:\nCultures of embryonic hippocampal neurons were prepared using a standard procedure. Briefly, hippocampi were dissected from E18 embryonic rats (Sprague-Dawley) and digested with papain for 15 min at 37°C." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6893-6177" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5265-6306" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-22" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2533" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

